    <node id="n2">
      <data key="d6">
        <y:GenericNode configuration="com.yworks.flowchart.annotation">
          <y:Geometry height="272.1514041514041" width="380.1547619047619" x="-413.7415555364775" y="102.83054792429795"/>
          <y:Fill color="#E8EEF7" color2="#B7C9E3" transparent="false"/>
          <y:BorderStyle color="#000000" type="line" width="1.0"/>
          <y:NodeLabel alignment="center" autoSizePolicy="content" fontFamily="Dialog" fontSize="12" fontStyle="plain" hasBackgroundColor="false" hasLineColor="false" height="241.46875" modelName="custom" textColor="#000000" visible="true" width="342.21484375" x="18.969959077380963" y="15.341327075702054">Nightly test script
CFS_SOURCE_DIR/ctest_scripts/nightly_test.cmake 
called by ctest either from /etc/crontab on wiki.mdmt
or by provisioner scripts in Vagrant boxes.

In any case, a log file of the entire testing progress is
written to SITE_DIR/logs/nightly_test.log

Before nightly testing starts, it is advisable to reset
the permissions of all involved directories, so that
they are writeable by the test user. This operation
is performed on e.g. on wiki by the script
SITE_DIR/set_permissions.cmake
which is called with root priviledges from /etc/crontab.

We use CTest instead of CMake, because it possible to
set environment variables for sub-processes with CTest.<y:LabelModel>
              <y:SmartNodeLabelModel distance="4.0"/>
            </y:LabelModel>
            <y:ModelParameter>
              <y:SmartNodeLabelModelParameter labelRatioX="0.0" labelRatioY="0.0" nodeRatioX="0.0" nodeRatioY="0.0" offsetX="0.0" offsetY="0.0" upX="0.0" upY="-1.0"/>
            </y:ModelParameter>
